06:12.460 --> 06:15.980
I can't be everything he needs.

06:20.660 --> 06:23.379
These sandwiches taste of feet.

06:23.380 --> 06:24.979
Anyone for a top-up?

06:24.980 --> 06:28.299
Oh, no, thank you.
No, I really couldn't.

06:28.300 --> 06:31.259
Any more sherry,
I'll be shitting doilies.

06:31.260 --> 06:33.500
I'll have some.

06:36.420 --> 06:37.939
Incoming at nine o'clock.

06:37.940 --> 06:41.939
Insurance salesman, I'm thinking,
or ambulance chaser.

06:41.940 --> 06:44.179
We might get a free pen.

06:44.180 --> 06:46.459
Afternoon, ladies.
Thank you for coming.

06:46.460 --> 06:47.500
Wouldn't miss it for the world.

06:47.501 --> 06:48.899
Indeed.

06:48.900 --> 06:50.299
Did you know Irene well?

06:50.300 --> 06:53.259
Oh, very close, we were, at one time.

06:53.260 --> 06:54.699
Who's Irene?

06:54.700 --> 06:57.740
The lady who passed away
so tragically.

07:01.140 --> 07:02.260
So, when were you close?

07:02.261 --> 07:04.619
Back in the day, in the '60s.

07:04.620 --> 07:05.900
Too long ago to remember.

07:05.901 --> 07:10.020
No, please, do try. It's wonderful
meeting people who knew my mum.

07:11.980 --> 07:13.899
Your mum?

07:13.900 --> 07:15.179
Oh, well...

07:15.180 --> 07:18.259
Er, she loved travel, your mother.

07:18.260 --> 07:20.979
She did, especially in the '60s.

07:20.980 --> 07:22.739
We travelled together...

07:22.740 --> 07:24.379
all over,

07:24.380 --> 07:27.739
across Europe, North America...

07:27.740 --> 07:29.979
I hope you don't mind,

07:29.980 --> 07:33.339
but since we only brought my mother
back from Austria yesterday,

07:33.340 --> 07:34.939
would you mind saying a few words?

07:34.940 --> 07:39.739
No! That's something
you should do, surely.

07:39.740 --> 07:43.539
Well, she left when I was two. She
only got back in touch last year.

07:43.540 --> 07:46.060
Someone like you
could say so much more.

07:47.780 --> 07:49.100
Oh!

07:50.420 --> 07:51.740
Thanks.

